SIMPLE: multivalent
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Multivalent
<hw>Mul*tiv"a*lent</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Multi-</ets> + L. <ets>valens</ets>, p. pr. See
<er>Valence</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd>
<def>Having a valence greater than one, as silicon.</def> <sd>(b)</sd>
<def>Having more than one degree of valence, as sulphur.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Immunology)</fld> <def>Having multiple
antigen-binding sites; -- of antibody molecules.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Immunology)</fld> <def>Containing several types of
antibody, to protect against more than one disease; polyvalent; -- of
vaccines.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Multivalve</ent>⟦br⟧
